# Trivy CVE allowlist — keep tight, document every entry.
#
# Each block follows the same pattern : the CVE id, the *binary* it
# affects in our image, the reason we can't fix it at our layer, and
# what we'd track to remove the exception later.
#
# Rule of thumb : only ignore CVEs in code we vendor through a
# third-party (Chrome via puppeteer, browser engines, etc.). Anything
# in our own dependency tree gets patched via `pnpm.overrides` instead.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Go stdlib CVEs inside puppeteer's chrome-headless-shell
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# `puppeteer` (api dep, used by the Library module's Amazon book
# lookup) downloads Chrome + chrome-headless-shell at postinstall.
# Those binaries embed Go helpers (crash handler, telemetry shims) and
# Trivy decompiles them to flag the Go stdlib version. We can't bump
# Google's vendored Go without rebuilding Chrome ourselves — that's
# upstream's problem. Track on each puppeteer bump : if the next
# puppeteer release ships a Chrome with newer Go, these can drop.
#
# Reviewed for blast radius : the Go binaries only run when the api
# spawns chrome-headless-shell for an Amazon scrape. They don't sit on
# the request path and they don't terminate TLS. The CVE titles below
# are TLS-cert-validation / RegexDoS / archive-parser issues — none
# actionable through our HTTP surface.

# CVE-2025-68121 — crypto/tls: incorrect cert validation on session
# resumption. CRITICAL. Patched in Go 1.24.13.
CVE-2025-68121

# CVE-2025-58183 — archive/tar: unbounded allocation when parsing
# malformed GNU headers. HIGH. Patched in Go 1.24.8.
CVE-2025-58183

# CVE-2025-61726, CVE-2025-61728, CVE-2025-61729 — Go runtime/stdlib
# DoS surfaces. HIGH.
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61729

# CVE-2026-25679 — Go stdlib. HIGH.
CVE-2026-25679

# CVE-2026-32280, CVE-2026-32281, CVE-2026-32283 — crypto/x509,
# crypto/tls: DoS via crafted cert chains / TLS 1.3 keys. HIGH.
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32281
CVE-2026-32283

# CVE-2026-33811, CVE-2026-33814 — Go stdlib. HIGH.
CVE-2026-33811
CVE-2026-33814

# CVE-2026-39820, CVE-2026-39836 — Go stdlib. HIGH.
CVE-2026-39820
CVE-2026-39836

# CVE-2026-42499 — Go stdlib. HIGH.
CVE-2026-42499
